platformd-trustd NEWS
=====================

platformd-trustd 0.0.1 (unreleased)

  First milestone (T1, observability) of the platform-authentication state
  authority. See docs/platform-trust.md.

  * platformd-trustd: a system daemon that binds local boot identity and the
    logind sessions into read-only records and serves them over the Varlink
    interface io.platformd.Trust (GetBootEvidence, ListSessions,
    GetSessionTrust). It observes; it gates nothing and holds no secret.
  * trustctl: status, list-sessions, and session <id>.

  Not yet implemented: session lock state and freshness (T2), the
  pam_platformd.so authentication bridge (T3), boot measurement evidence — Secure
  Boot and TPM/PCRs (T4), and the D-Bus state API (T5).
